AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; Up here, the air is thin, but it makes the crust crispier than anything you\'ll find down in the valley. &gt;&gt; Is that why the vanguard sent me all the way up this peak? Just for a crispier crust?'

[00:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; Not just the crust. Look out there at the high mills. Those sails grind grain harvested from the lower terraces. The friction builds a unique heat that changes the flour entirely. Ordinary'

